>No; Alpha is little endian (as, obviously, is Intel).  SPARC,
>m68k and PowerPC are big-endian; MIPS and ARM can >be either.
AFAIK the Alpha and the POwerPC can do Both. For the PowerPC it doesn't matter
(just have to tell him). On the Alpha the best mode is Big Endian - little
endians slows the beast - afaik being little endian 32 bits is the best way to
slow the beast : exactly what NT does.
